<i>Posted by Terrak on 01-11-2002 06:18 PM:</i>

<p><b> 
</b></p>

<p><br>
Well, ya, actually.  Speaking as a crafter I'm really in favor of getting the metals sooner than later but they've got a massive list of things that they had wanted in before the end of the year.  A good number of them got pushed back by one balance issue or another so that puts them into a backlog of where they want to be.  Shapeshifting phase 1 is, actually, as far as I can tell, of critical importance since it eventually leads to a major ability of Assassins (disguise) to say nothing of higher level abilities for other classes that will get phase 2 shapeshifting.<br>
<br>
Climb is another ability that they wanted in before year end that got pushed back and just one more component of completing the assassin classes.<br>
<br>
The Tradeskill Dev has this as one of his top items but he also needs programming resource which is, I think, spread a bit thin and the flu that's going around lately isn't helping (it's even striking up here in the North East now).<br>
<br>
I have every confidence that the new materials will be going in soon but when you've got a couple of thousand of people screaming at you that their issue is the most important you have to make decisions and no matter which decision you make you're going to piss off someone.<br>
<br>
<br>
edit: just wanted to note -- not taken as a flame.  It's frustrating for me too, believe me.</p>

